<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: Abortion is extremely common. In America, for example, one in three women will have an abortion in their lifetime, yet the strong emotions sparked by the topic -- and the highly politicized rhetoric around it -- leave little room for thoughtful, open debate. In this personal, thoughtful talk, Aspen Baker makes the case for being neither “pro-life” nor “pro-choice” but rather &quot;pro-voice&quot; -- and for the roles that listening and storytelling can play when it comes to discussing difficult topics." name="description" />
